  "text": "Zemp et al. [CITATION_1] described an approach to characterizing the quality of ultrasound signals through the construct of GNEQ, a quantity defined by Barrett et al. [CITATION_2] and derived from earlier works on photon imaging [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] . The Zemp work defined GNEQ for the RF data, and then showed how this could be used to predict ideal-observer performance for the envelope signal in the limit of low-contrast tasks.",
